Articles.Content:
7 hours ago, Loren Pechtel said:

This mod goes a long way to avoiding needless clicks but I still have to EVA in order to get EVA reports.  I've got the [x] Science! mod installed that shows me what biome I'm over but that still means sitting there like a hawk on the EVA button.  I just got to Mun, I'm in a nearly polar orbit so I'll pass over everything in time.  Twice now I've passed over Polar Lowlands--and both times it's been so fast that I wasn't able to mash the EVA button in time.  And now I lost the Northwest Crater becuase my mouse wasn't right on the EVA button.

I use ScanSat just for this purpose. Having the body scanned will show you where the biomes are and you can get out just before you get there to ensure you can get the report in time.

2 hours ago, Puff3r said:

I use ScanSat just for this purpose. Having the body scanned will show you where the biomes are and you can get out just before you get there to ensure you can get the report in time. 

Is that a mod or tech I haven't unlocked yet?

This Mod + Science Alert + [x]Science = Win Win Win.

I have to say, I'm a huge fan of this mod, even though it doesn't seem to always fire, but still, it's good stuff. Unfortunately, just now, I found a wall of spam at the top of my player.log, just curious what it means: 

Missing method ScienceData::.ctor(single,single,single,string,string) in assembly /home/user/.local/share/Steam/steamapps/common/Kerbal Space Program/KSP_Data/Managed/Assembly-CSharp.dll, referenced in assembly /home/user/.local/share/Steam/steamapps/common/Kerbal Space Program/GameData/KerboKatz/ForScienceContinued/ForScienceContinued.dll

Cheers.

On 2/19/2016 at 9:04 AM, Loren Pechtel said:

Is that a mod or tech I haven't unlocked yet?

A mod, a very good one in fact, highly recommended!
